# 🌦️ Weather App

A sleek and responsive weather application that fetches real-time weather data, displays dynamic backgrounds based on the searched city, and provides autocomplete suggestions using three powerful APIs. Built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, and deployed via GitHub Pages.

## 🔗 Live Demo

👉 [Click here to view the live app](https://anshp05.github.io/WeatherApp/)  

---

## 📸 Screenshots

![Weather App Screenshot](./weatherAppScreenshot.png)

---

## ✨ Features

- 🔍 Search for weather by city name
- 🏙️ City autocomplete suggestions
- 🌡️ Displays temperature, condition, humidity, and wind speed
- 🔁 Toggle between Imperial and Metric units
- 📸 Dynamic background images powered by Unsplash
- ⚡ Real-time data from OpenWeatherMap
- 📍 Automatic location detection using Geolocation

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** HTML, CSS, JavaScript (Vanilla)
- **APIs Used:**
  - [OpenWeatherMap API](https://openweathermap.org/api) — real-time weather data
  - [Unsplash API](https://unsplash.com/developers) — dynamic background images based on city
  - [GeoDB Cities API](https://rapidapi.com/wirefreethought/api/geodb-cities) — location autocomplete suggestions
- **Deployment:** GitHub Pages

---

## ⚙️ Background Image Note

If the Unsplash API fails to return a city image, a fallback background (`background.jpg`) stored locally in the project root will be used. Make sure `background.jpg` exists in the root directory to avoid blank backgrounds.

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/AnshP05/weather-app.git
cd weather-app
2. Open index.html in your browser (or use Live Server in VS Code)

